"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-03-10-Like-No-Other-Interview-with-Olympic-champion-Gong-Lijiao-1rR6jwOEug8-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Chinese shot put athlete Gong Lijiao is preparing for her fourth Olympic Games in Paris this year. The 35-year-old, a three-time Olympic medalist, gave her best performance at the 2020 Tokyo Olympic Games, winning her first Olympic gold medal in the women's shot put event. In this episode of our series Like No Other featuring Chinese women, Gong shares her perspectives on achieving personal goals and overcoming challenges -- both on and off the field.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"